    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Surface elemental analysis technique widely used for identification and characterization of pigments in conservation science. It is an x-ray fluorescence technique in which an incident beam strikes a sample below the critical angle of external total reflection for X-rays resulting in nearly total reflection of the excitation beam photons.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
